  - q: "What is a fractional chief of staff?"
    a: "A fractional chief of staff is a senior operator who delivers the chief-of-staff function part-time, typically 10–25 hours a week. They run the leadership operating rhythm, own one or two strategic initiatives, and keep board and investor operations disciplined, without the company carrying a full-time executive salary."
  - q: "How many hours a week does a fractional chief of staff work?"
